snippet.textDisplay:
I still feel the game is way clunkier than souls, I’ve played all the Fromsoftware titles of this genre (minus demons souls) and Sekiro, while fun, just feels like it forces you to play defensive. Bloodborne is my favourite of all, because it encourages you to be aggressive, but it doesn’t demand it. There’s enough variety to play how you want but lean into their intended style. Sekiro on the other hand very swiftly teaches you that if you can’t spam L1 you’re going to have a bad time.

Granted, it’s super impressive to see people master it like this video shows! Still an awesome title, just a little too restrictive for my taste.
